08/04/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Police began implementing tighter security measures at courts throughout the country on Monday (7 April). The measures followed a series of bomb threats at a number of larger courts. Now, police check every visitor while judges, prosecutors and lawyers enter and exit through specially designated areas prohibited for use by non-staff. ( Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa - 08/04/03; BTA - 07/04/03)
